            <fr:title text="Local criteria for quasi-coherent ideals">Local criteria for quasi-coherent ideals</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex> an ideal of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>. <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex> is quasi-coherent iff for all affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, the canonical factorisation
  
  <html:figure><fr:resource hash="43630480b02c4c3a9cdbc42434ba4fb6"><fr:resource-content><html:img src="/43630480b02c4c3a9cdbc42434ba4fb6.svg" /></fr:resource-content><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="preamble"><![CDATA[\usepackage {tikz-cd}\usepackage {quiver}]]></fr:resource-source><fr:resource-source type="latex" part="body"><![CDATA[
    \begin {tikzcd}
      {\mathcal  I(\mathrm {Spec} A)} \\
      {a \wedge  \mathcal  I(\mathrm {Spec}A)} & {\mathcal  I(\mathrm {Spec}A/a)}
      \arrow [two heads, from=1-1, to=2-1]
      \arrow [from=1-1, to=2-2]
      \arrow [from=2-1, to=2-2]
    \end {tikzcd}
  ]]></fr:resource-source></fr:resource></html:figure>

  induces an equivalence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \wedge  \mathcal {I}(\operatorname {Spec} A) = \mathcal {I}(\operatorname {Spec} A/a)]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>9</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  This is evident, since the condition exactly expresses that on each affine open <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}|_{\operatorname {Spec} A} = \widetilde {\mathcal {I}(\operatorname {Spec} A)}]]></fr:tex>.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
