            <fr:title text="Quasi-coherent ideals generate closed subschemes">Quasi-coherent ideals generate closed subschemes</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-86OJ/" title="Scheme" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-86OJ/" display-uri="schm-86OJ" type="local">scheme</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="/schm-TCWT/" title="Quasi-coherent ideal" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-TCWT/" display-uri="schm-TCWT" type="local">quasi-coherent</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {O}_{X}]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link href="/schm-OMYR/" title="Quasi-closed immersion" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-OMYR/" display-uri="schm-OMYR" type="local">closed immersion</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{\mathcal {I}} \hookrightarrow  X]]></fr:tex> produced by <fr:link href="/schm-5KCL/" title="Sheaf of ideals generate quasi-closed immersions" uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5KCL/" display-uri="schm-5KCL" type="local">Construction <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/schm-5KCL/" display-uri="schm-5KCL" /></fr:link> makes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{\mathcal {I}}]]></fr:tex> a closed subscheme of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors /><fr:date><fr:year>2025</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>9</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  The case when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is affine is clear. It is easy to see that when <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X = \operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {I} = \widetilde {I}]]></fr:tex> for some ideal <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, the closed immersion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C_{\mathcal {I}} \hookrightarrow  \operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> is exactly <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {Spec} I/A \hookrightarrow  \operatorname {Spec} A]]></fr:tex> induced by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A \twoheadrightarrow  I/A]]></fr:tex> (cf. <fr:link href="/idem-comm-FMRA/" title="Closed subspace of closed quotient" uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-FMRA/" display-uri="idem-comm-FMRA" type="local">Remark <fr:contextual-number uri="https://charloced.github.io/idem-comm-FMRA/" display-uri="idem-comm-FMRA" /></fr:link>). The case for general schemes is then evident from this.
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
